The paper discusses the technology stack involved in planning AV actions in the presence of pedestrians, which includes sensing, detection, recognition, and tracking. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Among these, Robotics and Computer Vision are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the topic of autonomous driving and pedestrian detection.
